questions.explanation:
`const` is a compile-time promise that the variable **will not be modified** after its initial value is set. Attempting to reassign is a compile error:

```cpp
const int MAX_SIZE = 100;
// MAX_SIZE = 200;  // error: assignment of read-only variable

// Common uses:
const double PI = 3.14159;
const std::string APP_NAME = "MyApp";

void print(const std::string& s) {  // s cannot be modified inside
    std::cout << s;
}
```
